cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the topic of copying Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and their vulnerability to adversarial examples attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of non-labeled data to copy the CNN, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
